Third-party notices
===================

centurymetadata reference implementation
----------------------------------------
Portions of this project are a TypeScript port of the centurymetadata Python
reference implementation, used under the upstream project's MIT license:

  Copyright (c) 2021 Rusty Russell
  Source: https://github.com/rustyrussell/centurymetadata/blob/master/LICENSE

The encode/decode logic in src/lib/centurymetadata.ts and test/roundtrip.mjs
is a derivative work of the following upstream files:

  - python/centurymetadata/constants.py    (wire format, preamble)
  - python/centurymetadata/encode.py       (compression, AES, ECDH, ML-KEM, signing)
  - python/centurymetadata/decode.py       (signature check, decryption)
  - python/centurymetadata/bip39.py        (BIP-32 derivation paths for CM_PURPOSE)
  - python/centurymetadata/validate.py     (accepted TYPE strings and per-type validation)
  - examples/EXAMPLES.md                   (XOR-PIR retrieval concept)
  - vars / README.md                       (protocol specification)

The byte-exact PREAMBLE constant in src/lib/centurymetadata.ts:156-178 and
test/roundtrip.mjs:18-41 is a verbatim mirror of upstream constants.py.

Underlying cryptographic primitives are provided by the following libraries,
each with its own license (see package.json for version pins):

  - @noble/curves        (secp256k1, Schnorr/BIP-340)   — MIT
  - @noble/hashes        (SHA-256)                       — MIT
  - @noble/post-quantum  (ML-KEM-1024 / FIPS 203)        — MIT
  - @scure/bip32         (BIP-32 HD derivation)          — MIT
  - @scure/bip39         (BIP-39 mnemonic → seed)        — MIT
  - fflate               (gzip / DEFLATE)                — MIT

Specifications referenced
-------------------------
This project implements protocols defined by external specifications. The
specifications themselves are not code and are referenced for clarity:

  - BIP-32  Hierarchical Deterministic Wallets
            https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0032.mediawiki
  - BIP-39  Mnemonic code for generating deterministic keys
            https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0039.mediawiki
  - BIP-340 Schnorr Signatures for secp256k1
            https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0340.mediawiki
  - BIP-380 Output Script Descriptors
            https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0380.mediawiki
  - BIP-329 Wallet Labels
            https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0329.mediawiki
  - NIP-06  Key derivation from mnemonic seed
            https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/06.md
  - FIPS 203 Module-Lattice-Based Key-Encapsulation Mechanism (ML-KEM)
            https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/FIPS/NIST.FIPS.203.pdf
